01:29:29.260 --> 01:29:32.730
of an addendum, just a
five-ish minute piece that

01:29:32.730 --> 01:29:35.500
goes a bit beyond this.

01:29:35.500 --> 01:29:38.260
Doing this by myself is a
little bit weird, I'm tired,

01:29:38.260 --> 01:29:40.060
and I will confess,
I got a little bit

01:29:40.060 --> 01:29:42.745
rattled when the police
came in to check in on me.

01:29:42.745 --> 01:29:43.870
Let's back up for a second.

01:29:43.870 --> 01:29:47.140
So I was talking
about two mysteries

01:29:47.140 --> 01:29:49.600
of the modern
cosmological model.

01:29:49.600 --> 01:29:52.270
One of them is this question
of why the universe is

01:29:52.270 --> 01:29:54.520
so apparently flat.

01:29:54.520 --> 01:29:58.180
The spatial sector of the
universe appears to be flat.

01:29:58.180 --> 01:30:00.055
And we had this expectation
that the universe

01:30:00.055 --> 01:30:05.400
is either radiation dominated
or matter dominated,

01:30:05.400 --> 01:30:09.420
which would give us the density
associated with radiation.

01:30:09.420 --> 01:30:11.462
If it was radiation
dominated, then the density

01:30:11.462 --> 01:30:13.920
of stuff in our universe would
fall off as the scale factor

01:30:13.920 --> 01:30:14.820
to the fourth power.

01:30:14.820 --> 01:30:16.570
If it's matter dominant,
it's scale factor

01:30:16.570 --> 01:30:18.067
to the third power.

01:30:18.067 --> 01:30:20.400
When you define a density
associated with the curvature,

01:30:20.400 --> 01:30:24.550
it falls off as scale
factor to the second power.

01:30:24.550 --> 01:30:28.110
And so if we look at the
ratio of the curvature density

01:30:28.110 --> 01:30:34.440
to any other kind of density, it
grows as the universe expands.

01:30:34.440 --> 01:30:37.530
So any slight deviation
from flatness we

01:30:37.530 --> 01:30:39.300
would expect to grow.

01:30:39.300 --> 01:30:41.430
And that's just confusing.

01:30:41.430 --> 01:30:44.430
Why is it when we make the
various measurements that we

01:30:44.430 --> 01:30:46.912
have been making for the
past several decades,

01:30:46.912 --> 01:30:48.870
all the evidence is
pointing to a universe that

01:30:48.870 --> 01:30:52.590
has a flatness of 0?

01:30:52.590 --> 01:30:55.980
If you sort of imagine that
the parameter kappa can

01:30:55.980 --> 01:30:58.360
be any number between
minus infinity to infinity,

01:30:58.360 --> 01:31:00.760
why is nature picking out 0?

01:31:00.760 --> 01:31:04.000
Another mystery is why is the
cosmic microwave background

01:31:04.000 --> 01:31:05.880
so homogeneous?

01:31:05.880 --> 01:31:08.460
We believe that the universe
was a very hot dense plasma

01:31:08.460 --> 01:31:09.660
at very early times.

01:31:09.660 --> 01:31:14.570
It cooled as the
universe expanded,

01:31:14.570 --> 01:31:21.740
and when we measured the
radiation from that cooling

01:31:21.740 --> 01:31:23.570
expanding ball of
plasma, what we find

01:31:23.570 --> 01:31:25.070
is that it has the
same temperature

01:31:25.070 --> 01:31:28.520
at every point in the sky
to within a part in 100,000.

01:31:28.520 --> 01:31:34.580
But when one looks at the
behavior of how light moves

01:31:34.580 --> 01:31:37.760
around in the early universe,
if the universe is matter

01:31:37.760 --> 01:31:39.740
dominated or
radiation dominated,

01:31:39.740 --> 01:31:43.280
what you find is that a piece
of the sky over here cannot

01:31:43.280 --> 01:31:45.650
communicate with a
piece of sky over here.

01:31:45.650 --> 01:31:46.850
Or over here, or over here.

01:31:46.850 --> 01:31:50.480
You actually find that
the size of the sky

01:31:50.480 --> 01:31:52.400
that, if I look at
a piece of sky over

01:31:52.400 --> 01:31:54.500
here, how much of the
universe could it talk to,

01:31:54.500 --> 01:31:56.220
it's surprisingly small.

01:31:56.220 --> 01:31:58.970
So how is it that
the entire universe

01:31:58.970 --> 01:32:00.110
has the same temperature?

01:32:00.110 --> 01:32:03.590
How is that they are apparently
in thermal equilibrium,

01:32:03.590 --> 01:32:08.260
even if they cannot
exchange information?

01:32:08.260 --> 01:32:11.380
So I spent some while
talking to myself

01:32:11.380 --> 01:32:13.710
after the cameras went out.

01:32:13.710 --> 01:32:16.420
So I'll just sketch
what I wrote down.

01:32:16.420 --> 01:32:19.270
A proposed solution to this,
to both of these mysteries,

01:32:19.270 --> 01:32:21.310
is what is known as cosmic
inflation, something

01:32:21.310 --> 01:32:24.790
that our own Alan Guth shares
a lot of the credit for helping

01:32:24.790 --> 01:32:25.930
to develop.

01:32:25.930 --> 01:32:31.130
So recall, if we have a
cosmological constant,

01:32:31.130 --> 01:32:33.730
then the scale factor
grows exponentially

01:32:33.730 --> 01:32:35.695
and the density of
stuff associated

01:32:35.695 --> 01:32:39.190
with that cosmological
constant is constant.

01:32:39.190 --> 01:32:42.540
As the universe expands,
the energy density

01:32:42.540 --> 01:32:44.290
associated with that
cosmological constant

01:32:44.290 --> 01:32:46.060
does not change.

01:32:46.060 --> 01:32:49.100
If our universe is dominated
by such a constant,

01:32:49.100 --> 01:32:52.390
then the ratio of density is
associated with curvature,

01:32:52.390 --> 01:32:54.970
the density associated with
cosmological constant, actually

01:32:54.970 --> 01:32:59.080
falls off inversely with
the curvature scale squared,

01:32:59.080 --> 01:33:01.450
and the curvature scale
is growing exponentially,

01:33:01.450 --> 01:33:03.970
it means that omega
c is being driven

01:33:03.970 --> 01:33:11.410
to zero relative to the density
in cosmological constant, as e

01:33:11.410 --> 01:33:12.390
to a factor like this.

01:33:12.390 --> 01:33:14.713
It's being exponentially
driven close to 0.

01:33:14.713 --> 01:33:16.630
You'd do do a little bit
of work to figure out

01:33:16.630 --> 01:33:18.505
what the timescales
associated with this are,

01:33:18.505 --> 01:33:21.280
but this suggests that if you
can put the universe in a state

01:33:21.280 --> 01:33:23.590
where it looks like a
cosmological constant,

01:33:23.590 --> 01:33:28.090
you can drive the density
associated with curvature as

01:33:28.090 --> 01:33:29.570
close to 0 as you want.

01:33:35.350 --> 01:33:38.420
Recall that a cosmological
constant is actually

01:33:38.420 --> 01:33:41.300
equivalent to there
being a vacuum energy.

01:33:41.300 --> 01:33:43.640
If we think about the
universe being filled

01:33:43.640 --> 01:33:46.940
with some kind of a scalar
field at early times,

01:33:46.940 --> 01:33:51.410
it can play the role of
such a vacuum energy.

01:33:51.410 --> 01:33:53.000
Without going into
the details, one

01:33:53.000 --> 01:33:55.070
finds that in an
expanding universe

01:33:55.070 --> 01:33:58.080
there is an equation of
motion for that scalar field.

01:33:58.080 --> 01:34:01.520
How the field itself behaves
is driven by a differential

01:34:01.520 --> 01:34:02.710
equation, looks like this.

01:34:02.710 --> 01:34:04.293
Here's your Hubble
parameters, so this

01:34:04.293 --> 01:34:06.650
has to do with a
scale factor in here.

01:34:06.650 --> 01:34:09.590
v is a potential for this
scalar field, which I'm not

01:34:09.590 --> 01:34:11.630
going to say too much about.

01:34:11.630 --> 01:34:13.885
Take this guy, couple it to
your Friedmann equations,

01:34:13.885 --> 01:34:15.260
and the one that's
most important

01:34:15.260 --> 01:34:16.630
is the first Friedmann equation.

01:34:16.630 --> 01:34:19.700
What you see is that v of
phi is playing the role

01:34:19.700 --> 01:34:22.310
of a cosmological constant.

01:34:22.310 --> 01:34:24.610
It's playing the
role of a density.

01:34:24.610 --> 01:34:27.860
So if we can put the
universe into a state where

01:34:27.860 --> 01:34:31.190
it is in fact being dominated
by this scalar field,

01:34:31.190 --> 01:34:33.290
by the potential associated
with the scalar field,

01:34:33.290 --> 01:34:35.660
it will inflate.

01:34:35.660 --> 01:34:38.540
A lot of the research in
early universe physics

01:34:38.540 --> 01:34:40.490
that has gone on over
the past couple decades

01:34:40.490 --> 01:34:43.670
has gone into understanding what
are the consequences of such a

01:34:43.670 --> 01:34:45.080
such a potential.

01:34:45.080 --> 01:34:46.480
Can we make such a potential?

01:34:46.480 --> 01:34:49.460
Do the laws of physics permit
something like this to exist?

01:34:49.460 --> 01:34:53.030
If the universe is in this
state early on, what changed?

01:34:53.030 --> 01:34:54.745
How is it that
this thing evolves?

01:34:54.745 --> 01:34:56.120
Is there is an
equation of motion

01:34:56.120 --> 01:34:57.745
here so that scalar
field is presumably

01:34:57.745 --> 01:34:59.480
evolving in some kind of a way?

01:34:59.480 --> 01:35:01.163
Is there a potential,
does nature

01:35:01.163 --> 01:35:03.830
permit us to have a field of the
sort with a potential that sort

01:35:03.830 --> 01:35:05.720
of goes away after some time?

01:35:05.720 --> 01:35:09.440
Once it goes away, what
happens to that field?

01:35:09.440 --> 01:35:12.450
Is there any smoking gun
associated with this?

01:35:12.450 --> 01:35:14.990
If we look at the
universe and this

01:35:14.990 --> 01:35:20.240
is a plausible explanation
for why the universe appears

01:35:20.240 --> 01:35:22.700
to be spatially flat and
why the cosmic microwave

01:35:22.700 --> 01:35:25.303
background is so homogeneous.

01:35:25.303 --> 01:35:26.720
Is there anything
else that we can

01:35:26.720 --> 01:35:30.020
look at that would basically say
yes, the universe did in fact

01:35:30.020 --> 01:35:32.720
have this kind of an expansion?

01:35:32.720 --> 01:35:34.430
Without getting into
the weeds too much,

01:35:34.430 --> 01:35:37.520
it turns out that if the
universe expanded like this,

01:35:37.520 --> 01:35:41.450
we would expect there to
be a primordial background

01:35:41.450 --> 01:35:44.420
of gravitational waves, very low
frequency gravitational waves.

01:35:44.420 --> 01:35:47.420
Sort of a moaning background
filling the universe.

01:35:47.420 --> 01:35:49.070
And so there's a
lot of experiments

01:35:49.070 --> 01:35:51.313
looking for the imprints
of such gravitational waves

01:35:51.313 --> 01:35:51.980
on our universe.

01:35:51.980 --> 01:35:53.930
If it is measured,
it would allow

01:35:53.930 --> 01:35:57.060
us to directly probe what this
inflationary potential actually

01:35:57.060 --> 01:35:58.580
is.

